# Frontend Number Serialization

When returning numeric values to the frontend, check whether the value can exceed
JavaScript `Number` safe range. If it can, convert it to `String` before returning
to avoid precision loss.

Safe range: `[-9007199254740991, 9007199254740991]` (`Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER`).

Example:

```java
// If amount or id may exceed JS safe range
response.setAmount(amount.toString());
response.setOrderId(orderId.toString());
```
